SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 120
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Britni Singleteary
to the standards recommendation committee for
English language arts.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-312, creates a standards
recommendation committee for English language arts; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-312(a), provides that the
governor shall appoint four members to the standards recommendation committee for English
language arts; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Britni Singleteary to serve on such
committee for a term that expires on December 31, 2025; and
WHEREAS, Britni Singleteary has taught English language arts and social studies within
the Dyer County School System since 2010; she previously served as a teacher with the
Weakley County School System for five years; and
WHEREAS, she received her Bachelor of Science degree in Human Learning K-8 from
the University of Tennessee at Martin and earned her Master of Arts degree in Leadership at
Bethel University; and
WHEREAS, a 2023 graduate of the WestTeach Leadership Program, Ms. Singleteary
was the Dyer County Elementary School Teacher of the Year in 2013 and the Fifth
Consolidated Elementary School Teacher of the Year in 2013 and 2020; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-312(b), provides that all
appointments to the committee "shall be subject to confirmation by the senate and the house of
representatives"; now, therefore,
